WEBVTT

1
00:00:50.342 --> 00:00:52.803
-Is it a girl?
- Yes.

2
00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:54.596
Show me its arm.

3
00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:57.558
- She bears the mark.
- No!

4
00:01:00.227 --> 00:01:03.730
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

5
00:01:06.149 --> 00:01:08.277
- Help me!
- I can't.

6
00:01:08.360 --> 00:01:11.154
- They're going to kill her.

7
00:01:19.037 --> 00:01:23.584
Oh. thank you. Ethna. Thank you.

8
00:01:32.092 --> 00:01:34.678
Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!

9
00:01:59.036 --> 00:02:01.538
You cannot
stop the prophecy!

10
00:02:01.622 --> 00:02:04.541
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

11
00:02:04.625 --> 00:02:09.463
- No. No!
- Where's the baby?

12
00:02:09.546 --> 00:02:11.965
The midwife.
Find that baby. Sorsha.

13
00:02:12.049 --> 00:02:15.427
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

14
00:02:15.469 --> 00:02:17.596
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

15
00:02:17.679 --> 00:02:19.765
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

16
00:02:19.848 --> 00:02:23.435
- Silence. wench.
- My baby will finish you!
- Kill her.

17
00:05:50.642 --> 00:05:52.644
Dada! Dada!

18
00:05:56.064 --> 00:05:59.359
-Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!

19
00:06:00.611 --> 00:06:03.864
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

20
00:06:03.906 --> 00:06:05.866
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

21
00:06:05.908 --> 00:06:08.202
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

22
00:06:13.207 --> 00:06:15.751
Come on.

23
00:06:18.086 --> 00:06:21.131
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

24
00:06:21.215 --> 00:06:24.134
But. Dada. it's a baby.

25
00:06:24.218 --> 00:06:29.014
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

26
00:06:29.097 --> 00:06:32.643
- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?

27
00:06:32.726 --> 00:06:35.062
Daikinis are big.

28
00:06:35.103 --> 00:06:38.232
- Giants who live far away.

29
00:06:38.315 --> 00:06:40.609
Oh. she's so cute.

30
00:06:40.692 --> 00:06:44.738
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

31
00:06:44.780 --> 00:06:50.035
We'll push it downstream and forget
we ever saw it. Come on.

32
00:06:50.118 --> 00:06:52.037
- Come on.
- Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

33
00:06:52.079 --> 00:06:56.250
Shhh! It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

34
00:06:56.333 --> 00:06:59.795
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

35
00:07:01.338 --> 00:07:05.175
Mr. Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!

36
00:07:05.259 --> 00:07:07.219
Baaa!

37
00:07:10.639 --> 00:07:14.142
Ufgood. you still haven't
paid your debts to me.

38
00:07:14.226 --> 00:07:16.228
Where did you
get these seeds?

39
00:07:16.311 --> 00:07:19.064
Well. maybe I used magic.

40
00:07:19.147 --> 00:07:23.068
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

41
00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:26.738
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

42
00:07:26.780 --> 00:07:30.242
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

43
00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:33.370
- There's no law against that.

44
00:07:33.453 --> 00:07:38.625
Willow. you didn't leave
them alone by the river?

45
00:07:38.667 --> 00:07:41.003
Magic?
You'll need magic...

46
00:07:41.086 --> 00:07:43.463
if you expect to get your planting
done before the rains start.

47
00:07:45.507 --> 00:07:51.013
I will have this land. And you're
gonna end up working in the mines.

48
00:07:53.223 --> 00:07:56.977
- Baaa-

49
00:08:00.105 --> 00:08:03.108
Oh. you're lovely.

50
00:08:03.150 --> 00:08:05.152
- Yes. you are.

51
00:08:05.235 --> 00:08:09.698
- Kiaya!
- Oh. Willow!

52
00:08:09.740 --> 00:08:14.661
- Good girl. Good girl.
- Under no condition whatsoever...

53
00:08:14.745 --> 00:08:17.497
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

54
00:08:17.539 --> 00:08:22.294
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on. Come on.

55
00:08:22.377 --> 00:08:24.421
There we are. Come on.

56
00:08:24.505 --> 00:08:27.132
Hey. I will not be ignored!

57
00:08:27.216 --> 00:08:30.886
Mims? Ranon?

58
00:08:41.897 --> 00:08:44.024
- You're gonna be all clean.

59
00:08:50.697 --> 00:08:53.992
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

60
00:08:54.076 --> 00:08:56.662
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

61
00:08:56.745 --> 00:08:59.540
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

62
00:08:59.623 --> 00:09:02.543
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?

63
00:09:02.584 --> 00:09:05.629
That's right. He's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!

64
00:09:05.712 --> 00:09:09.758
- Willow. calm down.
- Calm down?

65
00:09:09.842 --> 00:09:11.885
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

66
00:09:11.969 --> 00:09:15.722
Love. the High Aldwin hasn't
picked a new apprentice in years.

67
00:09:15.764 --> 00:09:19.059
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

68
00:09:21.812 --> 00:09:25.482
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

69
00:09:25.566 --> 00:09:28.360
- Hold her while I get some milk.
- Oh. no. no. Oh.

70
00:09:35.993 --> 00:09:39.454
- Dada. she likes you.

71
00:09:46.461 --> 00:09:47.629
- Bye.

72
00:09:47.629 --> 00:09:50.757
- Bye.

73
00:09:50.799 --> 00:09:54.720
- Come on. kids. Let's go.

74
00:10:00.767 --> 00:10:04.354
I will now magic ally join the rings!

75
00:10:26.335 --> 00:10:28.921
- Whoa-ah!

76
00:10:33.717 --> 00:10:36.136
Thank you. son.

77
00:10:36.178 --> 00:10:41.225
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

78
00:10:56.406 --> 00:10:58.659
Give me a ripe one. Good.

79
00:11:04.873 --> 00:11:09.378
- And now. for my final amazing feat.

80
00:11:09.461 --> 00:11:14.299
- I will make this entire pig disappear!

81
00:11:22.349 --> 00:11:27.479
- Mims. see?
- Please. watch very closely.

82
00:11:27.563 --> 00:11:33.193
- Wuppitybairn. deru. deru!

83
00:11:35.445 --> 00:11:37.865
- Well-
- What happened to your pig?

84
00:11:40.576 --> 00:11:43.620
No!
Hey. come here. you!

85
00:11:48.041 --> 00:11:51.461
I had seen enough.

86
00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:09.855
Attention!
The High Aldwin...

87
00:12:09.938 --> 00:12:12.858
-will now make his choice
for his new apprentice!
- You'll be all right.

88
00:12:12.900 --> 00:12:16.361
Bring forth the hopefuls.

89
00:12:16.445 --> 00:12:18.864
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

90
00:12:18.947 --> 00:12:22.701
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

91
00:12:22.784 --> 00:12:25.245
Is this a joke?

92
00:12:25.329 --> 00:12:29.791
- Willow?

93
00:12:32.211 --> 00:12:37.674
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

94
00:12:37.716 --> 00:12:42.304
Forget all you know...
or think you know.

95
00:12:42.387 --> 00:12:46.391
All that your require
is your intuition.

96
00:12:46.475 --> 00:12:50.562
Now. the power
to control the world...

97
00:12:50.646 --> 00:12:55.150
is in which finger?

98
00:13:37.109 --> 00:13:41.655
- No apprentice this year!

99
00:14:02.050 --> 00:14:05.429
- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!

100
00:14:05.512 --> 00:14:08.432
Take Ranon in there. quick!

101
00:14:16.315 --> 00:14:19.276
- Mims!

102
00:14:20.652 --> 00:14:22.779
- Mims!

103
00:14:31.038 --> 00:14:35.876
- Mims!
- Dada-

104
00:14:37.127 --> 00:14:40.214
- I'm scared. Dada!

105
00:14:50.516 --> 00:14:53.101
Come on!

106
00:15:10.744 --> 00:15:13.705
- Vohnkar!

107
00:15:23.215 --> 00:15:26.134
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

108
00:15:28.470 --> 00:15:30.264
Dada! Dada!

109
00:15:33.600 --> 00:15:35.853
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

110
00:15:38.897 --> 00:15:42.693
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

111
00:15:50.075 --> 00:15:53.412
Kiaya!
Kiaya!

112
00:15:53.495 --> 00:15:56.498
- I'm here.

113
00:16:00.586 --> 00:16:04.214
- Oh. Kiaya.

114
00:16:04.298 --> 00:16:06.508
We can't keep
the baby. Kiaya.

115
00:16:06.550 --> 00:16:09.428
We have to take her
to the village council.

116
00:16:22.900 --> 00:16:27.821
Silence! One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

117
00:16:27.905 --> 00:16:30.282
And you can be assured
that they won't give up...

118
00:16:30.365 --> 00:16:32.326
until they find what
they're looking for!

119
00:16:32.409 --> 00:16:35.662
-It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?

120
00:16:35.746 --> 00:16:38.248
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

121
00:16:38.290 --> 00:16:43.420
- In the pit! In the pit!

122
00:16:43.504 --> 00:16:45.631
In the pit! In the pit!

123
00:16:45.714 --> 00:16:49.009
-In the pit! In the pit!
- Willow.

124
00:16:49.092 --> 00:16:53.430
- Willow Ufgood.

125
00:16:53.514 --> 00:16:55.974
Come forward.

126
00:17:01.647 --> 00:17:06.985
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

127
00:17:12.574 --> 00:17:14.743
- A Daikini child.

128
00:17:14.826 --> 00:17:18.038
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

129
00:17:18.121 --> 00:17:19.206
Yeah!

130
00:17:19.289 --> 00:17:22.584
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

131
00:17:22.668 --> 00:17:25.295
This child is special!

132
00:17:25.379 --> 00:17:29.675
This child must be taken beyond
the boundaries of our village.

133
00:17:29.758 --> 00:17:32.803
All the way across
the great river...

134
00:17:32.886 --> 00:17:34.972
to the Daikini crossroads.

135
00:17:35.055 --> 00:17:39.768
- Well. who'll do that?
- It seems only fair...

136
00:17:39.810 --> 00:17:43.188
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

137
00:17:43.272 --> 00:17:46.233
be the very man who
plucked it out of the river.

138
00:17:47.818 --> 00:17:50.445
- I nominate Willow Ufgood.

139
00:17:50.487 --> 00:17:53.031
No!

140
00:17:53.115 --> 00:17:56.660
I will consult the bones!

141
00:18:04.042 --> 00:18:09.548
- The bones tell me... nothing.

142
00:18:11.216 --> 00:18:15.137
Do you have any love
for this child?

143
00:18:23.562 --> 00:18:28.025
Yes. Yes. I do.

144
00:18:28.108 --> 00:18:32.529
- The bones have spoken!

145
00:18:32.571 --> 00:18:36.533
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

146
00:18:36.617 --> 00:18:40.704
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

147
00:18:40.787 --> 00:18:43.290
But you will need help.

148
00:18:43.373 --> 00:18:48.712
Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?

149
00:18:50.756 --> 00:18:54.885
- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.

150
00:18:54.927 --> 00:18:58.222
- Excellent choice.
- I'll go!

151
00:18:58.305 --> 00:19:00.766
Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

152
00:19:00.849 --> 00:19:03.560
No! Not vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

153
00:19:03.602 --> 00:19:06.813
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

154
00:19:14.821 --> 00:19:17.407
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

155
00:19:17.491 --> 00:19:20.869
And according to the bones...

156
00:19:20.953 --> 00:19:24.331
- Bh-
-That leader is...

157
00:19:24.414 --> 00:19:25.832
...you. Burglekutt!

158
00:19:25.832 --> 00:19:26.834
you. Burglekutt!

159
00:19:26.917 --> 00:19:30.379
vohnkar!

160
00:19:30.462 --> 00:19:34.550
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

161
00:19:34.633 --> 00:19:39.930
When I held up my fingers
what was your first impulse?

162
00:19:40.013 --> 00:19:43.934
- Well. it was stupid.
-Just tell me.

163
00:19:43.976 --> 00:19:48.438
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha! That was the correct answer.

164
00:19:48.522 --> 00:19:53.277
You lack faith in yourself.
More than anyone in the village.

165
00:19:53.318 --> 00:19:55.946
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

166
00:19:56.029 --> 00:20:00.868
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

167
00:20:02.828 --> 00:20:07.833
- These will protect you. They're magic!
- Acorns?

168
00:20:07.916 --> 00:20:11.920
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

169
00:20:15.007 --> 00:20:18.218
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

170
00:20:31.148 --> 00:20:35.611
- Are you scared. Dada?
- No!

171
00:20:35.694 --> 00:20:39.948
Even with fairies in the woods that'll
put you to sleep for a hundred years?

172
00:20:41.950 --> 00:20:44.077
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

173
00:20:44.161 --> 00:20:47.080
- Dragons?
- Trolls?

174
00:20:47.164 --> 00:20:50.584
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

175
00:20:50.667 --> 00:20:54.296
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

176
00:20:54.338 --> 00:20:57.508
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

177
00:20:57.549 --> 00:20:59.134
Me too. Me too. Dada.

178
00:21:00.719 --> 00:21:06.058
What a lucky father I am. I wish
I could take you bobbins with me.

179
00:21:09.144 --> 00:21:11.688
Good-bye. Dada.

180
00:21:13.732 --> 00:21:17.736
Go play!
Go on.

181
00:21:21.698 --> 00:21:25.244
We've never been apart.

182
00:21:26.286 --> 00:21:29.623
I miss you already.

183
00:21:30.958 --> 00:21:34.378
Don't worry. Kiaya.
I'll be fine.

184
00:21:34.461 --> 00:21:36.380
I'll be back
before you know it.

185
00:21:38.632 --> 00:21:41.385
Well. remember
to keep her warm.

186
00:21:43.428 --> 00:21:46.139
And... here.

187
00:21:48.267 --> 00:21:51.061
This will bring you luck.

188
00:22:04.241 --> 00:22:06.577
Good brave people!

189
00:22:08.412 --> 00:22:11.164
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

190
00:22:11.248 --> 00:22:15.961
Give the baby to the first
Daikini you see. then hurry home.

191
00:22:19.464 --> 00:22:23.051
Tuatha...
lokwathrak... tuatha!

192
00:22:23.135 --> 00:22:26.680
Going the direction the bird is flying!

193
00:22:26.763 --> 00:22:30.684
- Ooh.

194
00:22:30.767 --> 00:22:33.604
It's going back to the village!

195
00:22:35.439 --> 00:22:37.399
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

196
00:22:37.482 --> 00:22:39.735
Move out!

197
00:23:03.675 --> 00:23:07.137
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

198
00:23:07.221 --> 00:23:11.266
- We have to stop.
- Stop? Why?

199
00:23:11.308 --> 00:23:13.810
- The baby's sick.

200
00:23:17.773 --> 00:23:22.361
She's not sick!
Let me see.

201
00:23:22.444 --> 00:23:25.656
Uhaghh!
Take her! Take her!

202
00:23:28.242 --> 00:23:31.328
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

203
00:23:33.664 --> 00:23:35.332
Clean me up.

204
00:23:39.002 --> 00:23:42.214
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

205
00:23:42.297 --> 00:23:46.218
-Sorsha. you're useless!
-I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

206
00:23:46.260 --> 00:23:48.470
I'll find where
she hid the baby.

207
00:23:50.430 --> 00:23:52.683
Ah. General Kael. at last.

208
00:23:52.766 --> 00:23:57.479
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

209
00:23:57.563 --> 00:24:01.275
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

210
00:24:01.358 --> 00:24:06.822
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

211
00:24:06.905 --> 00:24:08.866
that continues
somehow to elude her.

212
00:24:10.784 --> 00:24:12.744
The baby of the prophecy?

213
00:24:12.828 --> 00:24:16.248
- The one that would destroy you?
- I need that baby alive.

214
00:24:16.331 --> 00:24:18.792
I must perform
the ritual that will...

215
00:24:18.876 --> 00:24:22.212
exile the child's spirit
into oblivion.

216
00:24:22.296 --> 00:24:25.048
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

217
00:24:25.090 --> 00:24:27.176
You'll do as I say. child.

218
00:24:33.599 --> 00:24:35.767
I read the signs.

219
00:24:35.851 --> 00:24:39.021
One day. I fear. your daughter
will betray you.

220
00:24:39.104 --> 00:24:43.275
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

221
00:24:58.999 --> 00:25:01.543
- Move!

222
00:25:01.627 --> 00:25:03.587
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

223
00:25:07.883 --> 00:25:11.595
- Come on!

224
00:25:21.188 --> 00:25:24.107
The Nelwyns have got the baby.
We've searched the village.

225
00:25:24.191 --> 00:25:27.152
But a group of them
Is on the road somewhere.

226
00:25:27.236 --> 00:25:29.071
They couldn' t have gone far!

227
00:25:29.112 --> 00:25:32.115
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

228
00:25:39.498 --> 00:25:42.209
Come. We'll keep to the woods.

229
00:26:20.998 --> 00:26:25.169
That's it!
It's the crossroads!

230
00:26:41.602 --> 00:26:44.563
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

231
00:26:50.068 --> 00:26:52.571
- What was that?

232
00:26:53.906 --> 00:26:56.700
Get the spears!

233
00:27:13.133 --> 00:27:15.093
- Uhh. Uhh.

234
00:27:15.135 --> 00:27:19.014
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

235
00:27:19.097 --> 00:27:21.517
Do you understand?

236
00:27:21.600 --> 00:27:23.477
- Water.
- Yeah.

237
00:27:25.604 --> 00:27:27.606
Hurry up!

238
00:27:31.610 --> 00:27:34.530
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks.

239
00:27:34.613 --> 00:27:38.075
It's a Daikini.
We're in luck.

240
00:27:38.158 --> 00:27:40.577
We can't give her to him!

241
00:27:40.619 --> 00:27:44.581
- Somebody put him there for a reason.
- We've got to get rid of her.

242
00:27:44.665 --> 00:27:47.251
- Those soldiers are after us.
- Shhh.

243
00:27:47.334 --> 00:27:50.212
He's looking right at us.

244
00:27:54.132 --> 00:27:56.134
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

245
00:27:56.176 --> 00:27:59.054
I'm somebody.

246
00:27:59.137 --> 00:28:03.475
Let me out of here. I'll take care
of the baby. 

247
00:28:05.310 --> 00:28:09.940
- I trust him completely.
- But he tried to strangle me.

248
00:28:09.982 --> 00:28:13.944
- I want to go home!
- No. Burglekutt!

249
00:28:14.027 --> 00:28:17.364
- We should wait!
- Are you challenging my authority?

250
00:28:17.447 --> 00:28:20.826
As far as this baby
is concerned... yes.

251
00:28:20.868 --> 00:28:23.912
Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.

252
00:28:23.996 --> 00:28:29.084
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

253
00:28:29.168 --> 00:28:31.378
That's a bad idea.
Very bad.

254
00:28:31.461 --> 00:28:34.882
- Dangerous out there.
- Get the gear. men.

255
00:28:34.965 --> 00:28:38.510
- vohnkar-
- It's not his decision!

256
00:28:38.594 --> 00:28:42.514
Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

257
00:28:42.598 --> 00:28:44.266
Don't let him
talk to you that way.

258
00:28:44.349 --> 00:28:46.435
Listen here. runt.

259
00:28:46.518 --> 00:28:50.480
While you're wasting time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.

260
00:28:50.564 --> 00:28:54.860
- Think about it!
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna-

261
00:28:54.943 --> 00:28:58.322
You're gonna what?

262
00:29:02.201 --> 00:29:04.786
Some day. Burglekutt.
Some day.

263
00:29:04.870 --> 00:29:06.872
Vohnkar. let's go!

264
00:29:10.542 --> 00:29:13.253
Meegosh. are you coming?

265
00:29:15.547 --> 00:29:19.134
- I'm staying.
- Come on. men.

266
00:29:19.218 --> 00:29:23.388
Burglekutt. Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

267
00:29:23.472 --> 00:29:26.141
just let me out of here.
Please!

268
00:29:26.225 --> 00:29:29.686
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear...
just for a minute.

269
00:29:29.728 --> 00:29:32.022
Get-
Well. at least get me some water!

270
00:29:32.064 --> 00:29:37.027
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two! 

271
00:29:37.110 --> 00:29:41.907
- What'll we do now. Willow?

272
00:29:41.990 --> 00:29:44.618
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

273
00:29:44.701 --> 00:29:49.498
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry... peck.

274
00:29:49.581 --> 00:29:53.335
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

275
00:29:53.418 --> 00:29:57.172
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

276
00:29:58.590 --> 00:30:03.095
- I'll throw it. and turn you to stone.
- Whoo-

277
00:30:03.178 --> 00:30:05.138
I'm really scared.

278
00:30:05.180 --> 00:30:08.058
No. don't! Don't!

279
00:30:08.100 --> 00:30:10.936
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

280
00:30:11.019 --> 00:30:13.689
Oh. I wouldn't
want to waste it.

281
00:30:13.772 --> 00:30:17.025
Ha!
Peck. peck. peck. peck.

282
00:30:17.109 --> 00:30:19.653
peck. peck. peck.
peck. peck!

283
00:30:48.265 --> 00:30:51.143
- What was that?

284
00:30:54.521 --> 00:30:58.233
Mornin'. boys.

285
00:30:58.317 --> 00:31:02.446
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

286
00:31:02.487 --> 00:31:05.866
I don't think I introduced
myself yesterday.

287
00:31:05.949 --> 00:31:09.411
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh-

288
00:31:09.494 --> 00:31:12.456
No. Meegosh.
Don't go near him.

289
00:31:12.497 --> 00:31:15.959
- He's dangerous.
- I am not.

290
00:31:16.001 --> 00:31:18.170
Good.

291
00:31:22.925 --> 00:31:25.219
Stop! Wait!

292
00:31:26.970 --> 00:31:29.723
- Whoa!

293
00:31:35.187 --> 00:31:39.691
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

294
00:31:39.775 --> 00:31:42.277
I suppose you're a warrior.

295
00:31:42.361 --> 00:31:44.863
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

296
00:31:44.947 --> 00:31:47.783
Humph.

297
00:31:47.866 --> 00:31:51.620
Say. uh- Could I have
some of that water?

298
00:32:01.338 --> 00:32:06.093
I don't know why I try.

299
00:32:10.889 --> 00:32:14.142
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares.

300
00:32:14.226 --> 00:32:16.144
- Here.
- Thanks. friend. Oh!

301
00:32:16.228 --> 00:32:18.605
- What's that?

302
00:32:18.689 --> 00:32:22.651
I'd say
two or three hundred horses.

303
00:32:22.734 --> 00:32:26.697
five or six wagons...
and about a thousand fools.

304
00:32:29.408 --> 00:32:33.203
- Thank you. Ohh-
- Come on. Meegosh.

305
00:32:37.541 --> 00:32:41.253
It's gonna be
all right. little bobbin.

306
00:32:47.217 --> 00:32:51.138
- Everything's gonna be all right.

307
00:32:54.474 --> 00:32:57.561
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

308
00:32:59.521 --> 00:33:01.899
Uh. pardon me.

309
00:33:01.940 --> 00:33:04.067
Uh-

310
00:33:09.698 --> 00:33:14.912
Excuse me. sir. We found one
of your babies in our village.

311
00:33:14.995 --> 00:33:17.915
Will you please
take care of her?

312
00:33:17.998 --> 00:33:22.419
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

313
00:33:23.837 --> 00:33:27.007
They thought you were
a woman. Airk.

314
00:33:27.090 --> 00:33:29.468
Well-

315
00:33:29.551 --> 00:33:34.097
-Madmartigan. what did you do this time?
-Nothing you wouldn't have done.

316
00:33:34.181 --> 00:33:36.558
I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

317
00:33:36.642 --> 00:33:38.477
At least I'm not
down there herding sheep.

318
00:33:38.560 --> 00:33:40.062
What are you doing this far north?

319
00:33:40.145 --> 00:33:42.147
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

320
00:33:43.148 --> 00:33:44.483
The castle?

321
00:33:44.525 --> 00:33:46.985
Bavmorda's troops are
crushing everything in sight.

322
00:33:47.069 --> 00:33:48.987
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

323
00:33:49.071 --> 00:33:51.323
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

324
00:33:51.448 --> 00:33:55.744
Madmartigan-
I still serve Galladoorn.

325
00:33:55.827 --> 00:33:57.788
You serve no one.

326
00:33:57.871 --> 00:34:00.123
Remember?

327
00:34:00.207 --> 00:34:03.418
Sit in your coffin and rot.

328
00:34:03.502 --> 00:34:06.547
- Hyah!
- Wait. Airk. You need me!

329
00:34:06.630 --> 00:34:09.049
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

330
00:34:09.132 --> 00:34:11.760
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...

331
00:34:11.844 --> 00:34:13.929
and stick it
on a pig pole!

332
00:34:31.446 --> 00:34:36.159
- I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

333
00:34:40.163 --> 00:34:43.959
We're running out of food.

334
00:34:44.042 --> 00:34:47.671
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

335
00:34:47.713 --> 00:34:50.716
You know why?
Nobody cares.

336
00:34:53.594 --> 00:34:57.139
Except me.

337
00:34:57.222 --> 00:35:01.435
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

338
00:35:01.518 --> 00:35:05.480
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

339
00:35:05.564 --> 00:35:08.525
I believe he would. Willow.

340
00:35:08.609 --> 00:35:11.153
He doesn't know
anything about babies.

341
00:35:11.236 --> 00:35:16.450
Right. But I know
a lot of women who do.

342
00:35:16.533 --> 00:35:19.453
If I had somebody in my life.

343
00:35:19.536 --> 00:35:23.123
a little daughter. perhaps.

344
00:35:23.207 --> 00:35:26.460
I might have a reason
to go on living.

345
00:35:29.713 --> 00:35:32.508
You can't leave me
in here to die.

346
00:35:32.591 --> 00:35:35.636
Not when all I want
to do is protect her.

347
00:35:48.941 --> 00:35:52.861
I feel better!

348
00:35:52.945 --> 00:35:56.657
-You've done the right thing! -Okay. All right. All right.

349
00:35:56.740 --> 00:36:01.203
- You gotta promise to feed her.
- Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

350
00:36:01.286 --> 00:36:06.291
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

351
00:36:06.375 --> 00:36:08.418
- Hee. hee. hee!

352
00:36:08.502 --> 00:36:13.382
- Wheee!

353
00:36:13.465 --> 00:36:16.718
She likes me.

354
00:36:18.804 --> 00:36:21.181
Here are her changing rags.

355
00:36:21.265 --> 00:36:23.475
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

356
00:36:23.517 --> 00:36:27.813
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

357
00:36:29.523 --> 00:36:33.068
- You wory too much. peck.

358
00:36:33.151 --> 00:36:37.072
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

359
00:36:37.155 --> 00:36:42.911
Now listen. boys- Willow.
You've done the right thing.

360
00:36:42.995 --> 00:36:46.373
And I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

361
00:36:52.880 --> 00:36:57.134
- Good-bye. little one.

362
00:37:05.851 --> 00:37:08.103
Please. take good care of her.

363
00:37:09.897 --> 00:37:12.733
I give you my word of honor!

364
00:37:19.406 --> 00:37:23.327
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

365
00:37:23.368 --> 00:37:27.623
If we hurry. we can be home by
tomorrow morning. We'll be heroes.

366
00:37:27.706 --> 00:37:31.210
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

367
00:37:31.293 --> 00:37:33.545
"Look. there's
Willow and Meegosh.

368
00:37:33.629 --> 00:37:35.839
The heroes have come home."

369
00:37:35.923 --> 00:37:39.009
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

370
00:37:39.092 --> 00:37:43.347
- Yeah. Medals.

371
00:37:43.388 --> 00:37:47.142
Meegosh-

372
00:37:49.019 --> 00:37:53.148
- Did we do the right thing?
- Absolutely.

373
00:37:53.232 --> 00:37:57.528
- There's nothing to wory about.

374
00:38:00.531 --> 00:38:02.824
Hyah! Ha!

375
00:38:02.908 --> 00:38:08.121
I stole the baby! I stole the baby!

376
00:38:08.205 --> 00:38:11.959
- Hyah!
- That's my baby!

377
00:38:12.042 --> 00:38:14.002
- Stop! Wait! Come back!

378
00:38:14.086 --> 00:38:17.256
Left. you stupid bird.
Left! Ha ha!

379
00:38:20.050 --> 00:38:23.303
- Ah!
- Ow!

380
00:38:23.387 --> 00:38:27.057
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

381
00:38:27.140 --> 00:38:30.477
- Come on. Meegosh!
- Ow!

382
00:38:31.478 --> 00:38:35.232
- Uhh-uh-huh-uh.
- Uhh. Oww!

383
00:38:36.525 --> 00:38:38.569
We'll outrun 'em!

384
00:38:43.323 --> 00:38:47.411
-Hey. ugly. wake up!- 

385
00:38:47.494 --> 00:38:49.955
Huh?

386
00:38:49.997 --> 00:38:55.127
- Stand your ground. He's our prisoner.

387
00:38:55.169 --> 00:38:57.963
Meegosh.
where's the baby?

388
00:38:58.005 --> 00:38:59.965
Bring the Nelwyns tome.

389
00:39:00.007 --> 00:39:01.425
All right. you heard her!

390
00:39:01.508 --> 00:39:05.304
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

391
00:39:05.345 --> 00:39:07.723
You are mine to toy with.

392
00:39:07.806 --> 00:39:11.310
Forward!

393
00:39:11.393 --> 00:39:15.189
- Gimme the rope.

394
00:39:15.272 --> 00:39:19.276
Where-
Where...

395
00:39:19.359 --> 00:39:21.653
did you get that baby?

396
00:39:21.695 --> 00:39:26.450
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

397
00:39:26.617 --> 00:39:29.786
Franjean. release the Nelwyns.

398
00:39:29.828 --> 00:39:34.124
-And stop pestering them.
- Uh-oh.

399
00:39:34.208 --> 00:39:36.293
Ahh-

400
00:39:38.545 --> 00:39:40.506
- Yaah!

401
00:39:44.760 --> 00:39:48.013
- You!

402
00:39:48.055 --> 00:39:53.143
Welcome to my kingdom.

403
00:39:59.316 --> 00:40:03.820
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

404
00:40:03.904 --> 00:40:07.157
Blora Danan told me.

405
00:40:07.199 --> 00:40:10.536
Blora?
Blora. Willow is here.

406
00:40:13.330 --> 00:40:18.877
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

407
00:40:18.961 --> 00:40:24.299
My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.

408
00:40:24.383 --> 00:40:29.304
Blora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

409
00:40:29.388 --> 00:40:34.142
- Me?
- Yes. She likes you.

410
00:40:35.561 --> 00:40:40.524
And Elora Danan knows you
have the courage to help us.

411
00:40:40.607 --> 00:40:44.194
Take my wand
to the sorceress. Find Raziel.

412
00:40:44.278 --> 00:40:48.532
She will guide you and Blora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen.

413
00:40:48.574 --> 00:40:51.702
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

414
00:40:51.743 --> 00:40:55.539
You need a warrior for
a job like this. I'm a nobody.

415
00:40:55.706 --> 00:40:58.959
Blora. you don't want me.

416
00:40:59.042 --> 00:41:02.754
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

417
00:41:05.716 --> 00:41:08.343
Hello?

418
00:41:15.684 --> 00:41:19.104
Blora Danan must survive!

419
00:41:19.146 --> 00:41:24.026
She must fulfill her destiny and bring
about the downfall of Queen Bavmorda.

420
00:41:24.067 --> 00:41:26.945
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

421
00:41:26.987 --> 00:41:31.366
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...

422
00:41:31.408 --> 00:41:35.996
of your village.
your children- everyone.

423
00:41:40.667 --> 00:41:44.171
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

424
00:41:44.254 --> 00:41:49.468
The choice is yours.

425
00:42:12.032 --> 00:42:16.286
- Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.
- Huh?

426
00:42:16.328 --> 00:42:20.582
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

427
00:42:23.168 --> 00:42:26.713
Listen. Meegosh.
Tell Kiaya I love her.

428
00:42:26.797 --> 00:42:31.343
- And I think of her every day.
- Willow-

429
00:42:31.426 --> 00:42:34.888
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

430
00:42:34.972 --> 00:42:37.599
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

431
00:42:37.683 --> 00:42:40.602
I hope so.

432
00:42:40.686 --> 00:42:44.273
Listen. be careful.

433
00:42:50.362 --> 00:42:54.908
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

434
00:42:54.992 --> 00:42:58.453
-I am the leader!
- How long will it take to find Raziel?

435
00:42:58.537 --> 00:43:03.000
Um. not long. She's been exiled
to an island just over those hills.

436
00:43:03.083 --> 00:43:06.170
- She's what?
- Exiled...

437
00:43:06.253 --> 00:43:10.090
by the evil Queen Bavmorda.

438
00:43:10.174 --> 00:43:12.801
Rool. You fool. He does
not need to know everything.

439
00:43:12.885 --> 00:43:15.470
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

440
00:43:15.554 --> 00:43:17.848
- You mentioned the island. the queen.
- Wait a minute.

441
00:43:17.890 --> 00:43:20.559
So?

442
00:43:20.642 --> 00:43:23.437
What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?

443
00:43:23.520 --> 00:43:26.148
Don't play with that wand.

444
00:43:26.190 --> 00:43:28.775
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

445
00:43:28.859 --> 00:43:31.320
Only a great sorcerer can use it.

446
00:43:31.403 --> 00:43:34.156
-Not a stupid peck like you.

447
00:43:34.198 --> 00:43:37.367
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

448
00:43:37.451 --> 00:43:39.745
- All right. then this way.
- Bah. nope.

449
00:43:39.828 --> 00:43:42.331
- This way.
- This way?

450
00:43:42.414 --> 00:43:46.168
- That's what I said.
- This way.

451
00:43:46.210 --> 00:43:49.671
- You know where you're going?
- Of course.

452
00:43:49.755 --> 00:43:52.466
With us as your guides
no harm with befall you.

453
00:44:02.893 --> 00:44:07.064
- Take it up!

454
00:44:08.565 --> 00:44:12.819
- We are not going in there!
- But Blora needs fresh milk.

455
00:44:12.903 --> 00:44:17.741
- And we are drenched.
- You are not in command. shorty. I am!

456
00:44:17.824 --> 00:44:21.411
- You hear me?
- Whoa!

457
00:44:59.157 --> 00:45:01.618
- Excuse me? Excuse me.

458
00:45:01.660 --> 00:45:04.621
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

459
00:45:04.705 --> 00:45:06.582
Get out of here. peck!

460
00:45:06.665 --> 00:45:09.001
Get outta here
or we'll cook ya!

461
00:45:22.389 --> 00:45:26.310
Ooh. look at her!

462
00:45:26.351 --> 00:45:28.645
I could use
a love potion on her!

463
00:45:28.687 --> 00:45:32.524
Franjean! Hey! Give me that
dust of broken heart.

464
00:45:32.608 --> 00:45:34.318
- Come on! Give it to me!
- Let go of me!

465
00:45:34.401 --> 00:45:37.779
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

466
00:45:41.950 --> 00:45:43.952
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

467
00:45:50.918 --> 00:45:54.671
Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

468
00:45:56.965 --> 00:46:02.095
You are so beautiful!

469
00:46:02.179 --> 00:46:05.807
- Your eyes! Your whiskers!

470
00:46:05.891 --> 00:46:08.519
- I have to kiss you!
-Rool!

471
00:46:08.602 --> 00:46:10.354
That dust of broken heart!

472
00:46:25.202 --> 00:46:27.412
Beer!

473
00:46:30.541 --> 00:46:32.668
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

474
00:46:37.256 --> 00:46:39.258
Hurry! Hurry!

475
00:46:39.341 --> 00:46:41.218
My husband's coming!

476
00:46:41.301 --> 00:46:43.345
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

477
00:46:43.428 --> 00:46:46.056
- How do I look?
- Not you!

478
00:46:47.266 --> 00:46:49.184
Where the hell
did you come from?

479
00:46:49.268 --> 00:46:51.520
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

480
00:46:51.562 --> 00:46:55.399
Don't I know you?
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.

481
00:46:55.482 --> 00:46:57.693
- While you were taking a pee-pee!
- Cover your face!

482
00:46:57.776 --> 00:47:01.405
- You are crawling with Brownies.
- I hate Brownies!

483
00:47:01.446 --> 00:47:04.283
Whoa!

484
00:47:04.366 --> 00:47:06.952
- Where is he? Where?
- Hello. dear.

485
00:47:07.035 --> 00:47:09.413
There's nobody here but
me and. uh. my. uh-

486
00:47:09.454 --> 00:47:11.874
- I'll kill him!
- ...my cousin. Hilda.

487
00:47:11.957 --> 00:47:14.209
- Hilda?
- Hilda.

488
00:47:14.251 --> 00:47:16.378
- Oh. Hilda!
- This is my husband. Llug.

489
00:47:16.461 --> 00:47:19.214
- Mmm... Big husband.
- Yes.

490
00:47:19.298 --> 00:47:21.133
- How do you do?

491
00:47:21.216 --> 00:47:23.594
Hilda! Ooh.

492
00:47:23.635 --> 00:47:25.762
Come on. girly.
Don't be shy.

493
00:47:25.846 --> 00:47:28.473
- Hey! Give her back!

494
00:47:28.557 --> 00:47:30.934
- Pecks make terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

495
00:47:31.018 --> 00:47:33.937
- They get too excited.

496
00:47:33.979 --> 00:47:36.607
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

497
00:47:36.690 --> 00:47:38.734
- Huh?
- Hey. hey. hey. hey!

498
00:47:38.817 --> 00:47:43.447
- Stop. please. Ooh.

499
00:47:43.530 --> 00:47:45.407
Come on.
Fight like a man!

500
00:47:45.449 --> 00:47:48.493
- Want to breed?

501
00:47:48.577 --> 00:47:51.580
Tempting. but no.

502
00:47:54.499 --> 00:47:56.460
Thank you.
Time to leave.

503
00:47:56.502 --> 00:47:58.462
- Bye. Hilda!
- Take them out.

504
00:47:58.504 --> 00:48:01.673
- Hey! Come along!

505
00:48:01.757 --> 00:48:04.343
- Careful. you lout!
- Move along!

506
00:48:04.426 --> 00:48:07.137
Gather pall these babies.

507
00:48:07.221 --> 00:48:09.473
That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

508
00:48:13.227 --> 00:48:15.354
That's not the one.

509
00:48:19.066 --> 00:48:21.818
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

510
00:48:21.902 --> 00:48:24.488
- Yes. Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

511
00:48:24.571 --> 00:48:26.156
No! Don't let her!

512
00:48:26.240 --> 00:48:27.699
Aah!

513
00:48:27.783 --> 00:48:30.661
I gave you an order. woman!

514
00:48:40.003 --> 00:48:43.465
You-
You're... beautiful.

515
00:48:43.549 --> 00:48:46.885
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

516
00:48:49.471 --> 00:48:51.974
You're no woman!

517
00:48:52.057 --> 00:48:53.892
- Now. honey. take it easy.
- Not a woman?

518
00:48:53.976 --> 00:48:56.854
- Gentlemen.
- Not a woman?

519
00:48:56.895 --> 00:48:59.690
- Meet Llug.

520
00:49:00.983 --> 00:49:03.026
- After them!
- Out of the way!

521
00:49:09.324 --> 00:49:10.576
- To the horses!

522
00:49:10.576 --> 00:49:11.660
- To the horses!

523
00:49:14.204 --> 00:49:16.665
Hey! What are you doing?

524
00:49:21.044 --> 00:49:22.963
- Hyah!

525
00:49:23.046 --> 00:49:26.967
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

526
00:49:30.429 --> 00:49:35.309
- He's not a woman!
- To your horses! Hyah! Hyah!

527
00:49:35.392 --> 00:49:37.769
Don't let them get away!

528
00:49:39.438 --> 00:49:42.858
- Madmartigan. stop!
- What?

529
00:49:54.661 --> 00:49:56.705
Hyah!

530
00:50:01.835 --> 00:50:04.338
Madmartigan.
I'm warning you-

531
00:50:06.381 --> 00:50:10.052
- Ow!
- Prepare to die!

532
00:50:33.450 --> 00:50:35.786
Madmartigan!
Stop!

533
00:51:05.858 --> 00:51:07.901
Franjean. help me!

534
00:51:12.531 --> 00:51:14.449
- Rool!
- Help!

535
00:51:14.533 --> 00:51:17.578
Rool! Rool.

536
00:51:18.745 --> 00:51:22.541
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

537
00:51:27.921 --> 00:51:30.174
- Come on. I am.
- Pull me in.

538
00:51:30.257 --> 00:51:32.718
Yeah. pull!

539
00:51:50.903 --> 00:51:52.905
You can't have her!

540
00:51:58.827 --> 00:52:00.537
Whoa!

541
00:52:05.250 --> 00:52:08.837
- Rool. this isn't funny!

542
00:52:08.921 --> 00:52:10.839
Help me cut the rope!

543
00:52:24.019 --> 00:52:26.772
Who-oa!

544
00:52:48.293 --> 00:52:50.879
Willow. stay down!

545
00:52:54.591 --> 00:52:56.635
Whoa!

546
00:52:56.677 --> 00:52:58.929
Whoa!

547
00:52:59.012 --> 00:53:00.931
Gone crazy?

548
00:53:01.014 --> 00:53:03.141
You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

549
00:53:03.225 --> 00:53:05.644
- We're getting off!
- Hyah!

550
00:53:05.686 --> 00:53:08.313
Oh! Hold on! Hyah!

551
00:53:31.128 --> 00:53:33.630
Whoa! Whoa!

552
00:53:36.800 --> 00:53:39.136
- Oh. Rool.

553
00:53:39.219 --> 00:53:42.890
Now we stop. peck.

554
00:53:42.973 --> 00:53:48.270
Stupid Daikini.
Ask him to stop the wagon.

555
00:53:48.312 --> 00:53:52.524
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

556
00:53:54.026 --> 00:53:56.528
I just saved that infant's life!

557
00:53:57.988 --> 00:54:00.324
Hah! Hah!

558
00:54:00.407 --> 00:54:02.367
Gather your wits. Come on.

559
00:54:02.409 --> 00:54:05.454
- Don't wory about me.
-Come on!

560
00:54:06.538 --> 00:54:08.707
- Get down!

561
00:54:08.790 --> 00:54:11.168
Uh. where am I?
Oh!

562
00:54:13.086 --> 00:54:15.172
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

563
00:54:31.688 --> 00:54:34.274
-Ah. Franjean!
- You better clear out. Willow.

564
00:54:34.358 --> 00:54:35.817
Before those troops come back.

565
00:54:35.859 --> 00:54:39.321
- Ah. my head!
- We don't need him. Blora.

566
00:54:47.746 --> 00:54:49.831
Madmartigan. wait!

567
00:54:49.873 --> 00:54:53.210
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

568
00:54:53.293 --> 00:54:55.254
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

569
00:54:55.337 --> 00:54:58.549
My help? What do you need my help for?

570
00:54:58.632 --> 00:55:00.801
You're a sorcerer!

571
00:55:00.884 --> 00:55:04.096
You're a great warrior.
and a swordsman.

572
00:55:04.179 --> 00:55:07.057
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

573
00:55:07.140 --> 00:55:10.394
Are you tying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

574
00:55:13.647 --> 00:55:18.569
- Hurry! Big dogs!

575
00:55:18.652 --> 00:55:22.906
Look. I'm sorry
I got angry.

576
00:55:22.948 --> 00:55:24.908
We wouldn't have
escaped without you.

577
00:55:39.089 --> 00:55:41.925
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

578
00:55:43.427 --> 00:55:47.055
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

579
00:55:48.098 --> 00:55:51.268
That way.

580
00:55:51.310 --> 00:55:54.938
You are drunk. and when you
are drunk you forget that...

581
00:55:55.022 --> 00:55:56.940
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

582
00:55:57.024 --> 00:55:59.234
Fine.
Then which way do we go?

583
00:55:59.318 --> 00:56:01.320
That way!

584
00:56:04.364 --> 00:56:08.911
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

585
00:56:08.952 --> 00:56:11.955
All right. all right. You can
follow me as far as the lake.

586
00:56:12.039 --> 00:56:14.249
But that's it!

587
00:56:14.291 --> 00:56:18.086
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

588
00:56:18.128 --> 00:56:23.300
Good. Mumbo-Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go and get me some eggs or something.

589
00:56:23.383 --> 00:56:26.011
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

590
00:56:32.726 --> 00:56:37.397
Kael. have you found the child?

591
00:56:37.481 --> 00:56:39.233
The search goes on. my queen.

592
00:56:40.317 --> 00:56:42.319
Why. with my powers.

593
00:56:42.402 --> 00:56:45.614
with the strength
of my great army.

594
00:56:45.697 --> 00:56:49.117
can you not find
one little child?

595
00:56:49.159 --> 00:56:51.495
We look even now.
It won't be long.

596
00:56:51.578 --> 00:56:54.957
Find the child.
Find the child!

597
00:56:54.998 --> 00:56:57.626
Time is running out.

598
00:57:01.797 --> 00:57:06.218
- Good night.

599
00:57:06.260 --> 00:57:09.596
She is kinda cute.

600
00:57:09.680 --> 00:57:11.431
When she's quiet.

601
00:57:12.850 --> 00:57:14.768
She's really a princess.

602
00:57:14.852 --> 00:57:18.856
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

603
00:57:18.939 --> 00:57:20.858
And I'm the king of Cashmere.

604
00:57:20.941 --> 00:57:24.736
Go to sleep. Willow.

605
00:57:24.820 --> 00:57:27.322
Good night. Madmartigan.

606
00:57:27.364 --> 00:57:30.367
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

607
00:57:30.409 --> 00:57:33.745
Uh- Uh! Oh!
Rats! Ra-

608
00:57:33.829 --> 00:57:36.748
Oh. Rool. you had
that stupid rat dream!

609
00:57:47.551 --> 00:57:50.262
Tuatha...

610
00:57:50.345 --> 00:57:52.514
Lawkathok...

611
00:57:52.598 --> 00:57:54.516
- Tuatha!

612
00:57:54.558 --> 00:57:57.311
Huh?
Willow?

613
00:57:58.395 --> 00:58:00.522
Willow?

614
00:58:02.274 --> 00:58:04.735
Oh. There you are.

615
00:58:04.818 --> 00:58:06.778
Madmartigan!

616
00:58:06.862 --> 00:58:10.199
'Night. Willow.

617
00:58:22.294 --> 00:58:24.296
This way! This way!

618
00:58:36.099 --> 00:58:38.060
What are you doing?

619
00:58:38.101 --> 00:58:40.479
I found some black root.
She loves it!

620
00:58:40.562 --> 00:58:43.482
Black root? I am
the father of two children.

621
00:58:43.565 --> 00:58:45.567
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

622
00:58:45.734 --> 00:58:48.779
Well. my mother
raised us on black root.

623
00:58:48.862 --> 00:58:51.406
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

624
00:58:51.490 --> 00:58:54.243
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

625
00:58:54.284 --> 00:58:57.246
She's Blora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

626
00:58:57.287 --> 00:58:59.623
And the last thing she's gonna
want is a hairy chest!

627
00:59:03.794 --> 00:59:05.838
Did you see what he did?

628
00:59:05.921 --> 00:59:09.174
He stole our black root. I'll get
some more. don't wory about it.

629
00:59:14.012 --> 00:59:17.349
- There it is! The island!

630
00:59:19.560 --> 00:59:21.478
We made it.

631
00:59:21.562 --> 00:59:26.108
We have led you to
the island of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

632
00:59:26.191 --> 00:59:30.445
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat. 

633
00:59:48.505 --> 00:59:50.507
Well. looks like
I got you here.

634
00:59:50.591 --> 00:59:53.051
You!
What did you do?

635
00:59:53.135 --> 00:59:56.138
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs! Huh?

636
00:59:56.221 --> 00:59:58.182
I found a boat.
We're all set.

637
00:59:58.265 --> 01:00:02.186
Good. Take these two lizards
out and drown them.

638
01:00:02.269 --> 01:00:05.606
- Who are you calling lizards?
- Heh? Heh?

639
01:00:07.691 --> 01:00:10.360
Your mother was lizard!

640
01:00:13.363 --> 01:00:15.866
- Good-bye. Sticks.

641
01:00:18.535 --> 01:00:21.455
If you really are a princess.

642
01:00:21.538 --> 01:00:24.499
take care of him.

643
01:00:30.839 --> 01:00:34.134
- Madmartigan!
- What?

644
01:00:34.218 --> 01:00:36.094
Thanks.

645
01:00:45.604 --> 01:00:48.148
Hey! Aah!

646
01:00:48.190 --> 01:00:51.568
-Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turnaround!

647
01:00:52.736 --> 01:00:55.739
- It's all right. Blora.

648
01:00:55.822 --> 01:00:58.242
- Go to sleep.

649
01:00:58.325 --> 01:01:00.661
- Nobody'll find you here.

650
01:01:00.744 --> 01:01:02.329
I'll be back with
Fin Raziel very soon.

651
01:01:02.371 --> 01:01:05.707
We will guard her
with our meager lives.

652
01:01:34.027 --> 01:01:36.864
Raziel!

653
01:01:36.947 --> 01:01:40.742
Fin Raziel!
I have to talk to you. please!

654
01:01:44.663 --> 01:01:47.249
Raziel!

655
01:01:52.087 --> 01:01:55.757
She's not here.

656
01:01:58.760 --> 01:02:00.679
- Aah!

657
01:02:00.762 --> 01:02:04.308
Get back! Who are you?

658
01:02:05.434 --> 01:02:08.312
Who are you?

659
01:02:10.731 --> 01:02:13.817
- I'm Willow Ufgood.
- What are you doing here?

660
01:02:13.901 --> 01:02:17.571
I've come to find the great
sorceress. Fin Raziel.

661
01:02:17.654 --> 01:02:20.240
That's me!
I'm Raziel!

662
01:02:22.284 --> 01:02:24.203
This can't be right!

663
01:02:24.286 --> 01:02:27.789
One of Bavmorda's spells
transformed me.

664
01:02:30.083 --> 01:02:32.669
Believe me. it could
have been worse!

665
01:02:32.753 --> 01:02:38.550
Oh. Well. this wand is for you.
It's from Cherlindrea.

666
01:02:38.634 --> 01:02:43.138
Then the prophecy is true.
The princess has been born.

667
01:02:43.222 --> 01:02:45.182
Take me to her.

668
01:02:47.726 --> 01:02:50.479
It is Blora Danan.

669
01:02:50.562 --> 01:02:53.482
Isn't she beautiful?

670
01:02:53.565 --> 01:02:56.527
Isn't she beautiful?

671
01:02:56.610 --> 01:03:00.113
- That's Raziel?
- I don't know. I-

672
01:03:00.197 --> 01:03:02.449
I expected something
more grand. Less. uh-

673
01:03:02.491 --> 01:03:04.451
- Fuzzy.
- Fuzzy!

674
01:03:04.535 --> 01:03:08.330
You must use the wand.
Turn me back into my human form.

675
01:03:08.413 --> 01:03:11.750
- What do I do?
- You mean you're not a sorcerer?

676
01:03:12.960 --> 01:03:15.462
Yes. Sort a.

677
01:03:15.546 --> 01:03:18.048
-I'm a farmer.

678
01:03:18.131 --> 01:03:20.050
But I do know a few tricks.

679
01:03:20.092 --> 01:03:25.639
Tricks? Cherlindrea sent you?
You must learn real magic.

680
01:03:25.764 --> 01:03:29.810
- Horses! Horses!

681
01:03:29.893 --> 01:03:32.396
Quick! Take her!
Hurry! Hurry!

682
01:03:41.196 --> 01:03:44.157
I knew he was a traitor!

683
01:03:46.743 --> 01:03:49.454
- Sorry about this. peck.
- Keep your mouth shut!

684
01:03:50.497 --> 01:03:53.292
Told you we'd find him
without your help.

685
01:03:53.375 --> 01:03:55.335
- Give me that baby.
- No!

686
01:03:58.797 --> 01:04:02.759
- Give her back!
- Leave me alone! Don't touch me!

687
01:04:08.682 --> 01:04:10.559
This is the one
we're looking for.

688
01:04:10.642 --> 01:04:14.021
- We must take it back to Nockmaar.

689
01:04:16.815 --> 01:04:18.734
Lose your skirt?

690
01:04:26.408 --> 01:04:28.368
I've still got what counts.

691
01:04:28.410 --> 01:04:30.746
Not for long.

692
01:04:36.585 --> 01:04:40.130
- Bring him.
- Over here!

693
01:04:57.814 --> 01:05:00.567
We'll never keep up
with those horses.

694
01:05:00.609 --> 01:05:02.569
Then we will
have to track them.

695
01:05:02.611 --> 01:05:04.029
That would take forever.

696
01:05:04.112 --> 01:05:06.865
Besides. even if we find them.
they'll catch us.

697
01:05:06.907 --> 01:05:10.118
stick us in cages. torture us
and finally devour us.

698
01:05:10.202 --> 01:05:12.162
Are you suggesting
we go home?

699
01:05:12.246 --> 01:05:15.165
- Nah. This is more fun!
- All right.

700
01:05:15.249 --> 01:05:17.167
Fine. then.
Come on!

701
01:05:30.973 --> 01:05:34.434
I'm worried about Blora.
She doesn't sound good.

702
01:05:34.476 --> 01:05:37.271
Hurry! Practice
the chant I taught you!

703
01:05:37.312 --> 01:05:43.110
- Tanna... looatha- Oh. I can't
remember the middle part.

704
01:05:43.193 --> 01:05:45.237
Locktwaar!

705
01:05:45.279 --> 01:05:48.282
That's the word
that pleads for change.

706
01:05:48.365 --> 01:05:50.325
Locktwaar.

707
01:05:53.996 --> 01:05:57.165
Blora's cold and hungry.
She knows me.

708
01:05:57.249 --> 01:05:59.168
Please. let me
take care of her.

709
01:05:59.251 --> 01:06:01.378
I don't need help
from a peck.

710
01:06:05.132 --> 01:06:09.178
- What are you staring at?
- Your leg.

711
01:06:09.261 --> 01:06:11.638
I'd like to break it.

712
01:06:11.680 --> 01:06:16.560
You may find that difficult while
I'm up here and you're down there.

713
01:06:19.688 --> 01:06:21.899
I hate that woman.

714
01:06:54.556 --> 01:06:56.642
Hyah!

715
01:07:00.437 --> 01:07:03.232
- I found it. Kael.

716
01:07:04.358 --> 01:07:07.402
That should make
my mother happy.

717
01:07:07.486 --> 01:07:10.489
What are they gonna do to her?

718
01:07:23.043 --> 01:07:25.712
Hither walha...

719
01:07:25.796 --> 01:07:29.341
bairn derubordak...

720
01:07:29.424 --> 01:07:31.343
- bellanockt.

721
01:07:31.426 --> 01:07:34.304
That's magic?
Smells terrible.

722
01:07:34.388 --> 01:07:37.599
- It's the life spark. It forms after-
- Well. it stinks!

723
01:07:37.683 --> 01:07:40.853
- This whole thing stinks!
- Ignore him. Willow.

724
01:07:40.936 --> 01:07:43.939
- He's a fool!
- If only I had a sword!

725
01:07:44.022 --> 01:07:47.109
- If only you'd quit talking about it.

726
01:07:47.192 --> 01:07:50.571
Willow. you must transform me
to my human self.

727
01:07:50.612 --> 01:07:53.448
But. Raziel.
I'm not ready yet.

728
01:07:53.532 --> 01:07:56.743
You'd better be.
Get me down.

729
01:08:00.372 --> 01:08:02.791
Ow!

730
01:08:05.419 --> 01:08:08.422
Why don't you help me get out of here
instead of chattering with that muskrat?

731
01:08:08.505 --> 01:08:11.258
Muskrat!
When I change back...

732
01:08:11.300 --> 01:08:15.262
to my former self.
I will crush this army.

733
01:08:15.345 --> 01:08:18.015
and take Blora Danan
to Tir Asleen...

734
01:08:18.098 --> 01:08:20.684
where she will be safe.

735
01:08:20.767 --> 01:08:23.103
- Ow!

736
01:08:23.145 --> 01:08:25.105
What'd you bite me for?

737
01:08:25.147 --> 01:08:28.483
You need three drops
of your blood to put in the potion.

738
01:08:28.567 --> 01:08:31.862
- Well. you coulda warned me.

739
